gate: OPEN
sprint: S05
track: A
task: A3
title: "feat(delivery): UPS XAV result cache — hashed address key, TTL 24h"
repos: [crop-parts-services]
priority: high
refs:
  - S02 hypothesis C + lever L1 (highest-leverage fix)
  - S02 lesson: ups_xav_no_cache
  - INVARIANTS.md: "Address strings are PII — cache keys hashed, no raw addresses in logs"
requires: [BUN_HONO_CLOUDRUN, SECURITY]

description: |
  No result cache on UPS XAV — identical addresses re-validated on every checkout
  attempt. S02 ranked this lever L1 (highest leverage): cache hit eliminates full
  UPS round-trip (~400–700ms). Cache key = SHA-256 of normalized address fields.
  TTL = 24h for VALID, 5min for INVALID (user may fix and retry).

ground_truth:
  file: CROP-parts-services/services/delivery/src/providers/ups/ups-address.ts
  line: 30   # fetchWithRetry — no cache check before call

scope:
  in:
    - ups-address.ts — check cache before UPS call; store result after
    - Address normalization (lowercase, trim, canonical field order) — deterministic key
    - Cache key = SHA-256(normalized address JSON) — never raw address as key
    - Cache backend: reuse shared cache adapter from A2
    - TTL: 24h VALID / 5min INVALID
    - Unit tests: cache hit + cache miss + normalization determinism
  out:
    - FE changes
    - Raw address strings in any log or Sentry event (blocked by INVARIANTS.md)

invariants:
  - Raw address MUST NOT appear in cache keys, logs, or Sentry events
  - Cache key deterministic for equivalent addresses regardless of field order
  - PII retention: cached entries expire; no persistent address storage

acceptance:
  - Identical address second checkout → cached result, no UPS call
  - Cache key is SHA-256 hash — confirmed in test
  - INVALID cached 5min, VALID 24h
  - No raw address in logs

dep: A2   # reuses shared cache adapter
output: ups-address.ts + normalization util + cache integration + unit tests
